---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Best International Schools in Jakarta | ISJ Guide"
  description="A guide to international schools in Jakarta for expat families. Compare curricula, fees, and facilities to find the right school for your child."
  canonicalUrl="/insights/best-international-schools-jakarta"
  category="Jakarta Life"
  categoryHref="/insights"
  heroImage="/images/insights/jakarta-skyline-hero.jpg"
  heroAlt="Jakarta skyline at dusk with residential neighbourhoods in the foreground"
  author="Darren Brown"
  publishedDate="15 February 2026"
  summary="Choosing an international school in Jakarta is one of the most consequential decisions a relocating family will make. This guide covers the schools expat families actually choose, compares 72 schools by curriculum, location, and fees, and walks through the neighbourhoods, the commute realities, and the questions worth asking before you sign anything."
>

  <p class="text-right -mt-6 mb-6 text-[9px] text-charcoal-muted/30"><a href="https://www.pexels.com/@tomfisk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="hover:text-charcoal-muted/50 transition-colors">Photo: Tom Fisk / Pexels</a></p>

  <p>
    We aren't here to list every school in Jakarta. Instead, we've curated a shortlist of the contenders that are typically popular destinations for expats in Jakarta: the institutions truly worth a closer look and a campus visit.
  </p>

  <p>
    When choosing, three things matter most: <strong>curriculum fit</strong> (British, IB, American, each shaping how your child learns and where they can transfer), <strong>commute</strong> (in Jakarta, anything over 20 minutes each way will grind you down), and <strong>age range</strong> (if the school stops at Year 8 or Year 6, you need a plan for what comes next). Fees range from $4,500 to $39,000, but the most expensive school isn't necessarily the best fit for your family.
  </p>

  <h2>Where Do the Expats Live?</h2>

  <p>
    Where you live and which school you choose are decisions that need to be made together. Jakarta's traffic means that a 5km commute can take 45 minutes at the wrong time of day. For real commute time data comparing ISJ, JIS, BSJ, and AIS to offices and malls across the city, see the <a href=/insights/jakarta-school-commute-times>Jakarta school commute times</a> guide. The sections below outline each area and the schools nearby.
  </p>

